article.headline: East Tenn. St. 92, Western Carolina 83
article.story: JOHNSON CITY, Tenn. (AP) -- Ben Rhoda and Tim Smith combined for 46 points to lead East Tennessee State to a 92-83 victory Monday night over Western Carolina. ETSU (8-16, 4-10 Southern Conference) led the entire game but was only ahead 85-81 with 2:52 left after a basket by Trey Hopkins of the Catamounts (8-18, 3-10). The Bucs then scored on a layup by Smith and a layup by James Anthony after a steal by Travis Strong. Rhoda finished with a career-high 23 points, and Smith also had 23. Dillion Sneed ended with 19 during 40 minutes of play and Andrew Reed scored 16. Hopkins had a career-high 25 points for the Catamounts, who stayed closed by hitting 11 of 31 3-pointers. Rans Brempong added 15 for Western Carolina and David Berghoefer had 14. ETSU led by 23 points in the first half, but the Catamounts closed the half on a 21-6 run to trail 49-41 at the half.
